1 1. The life science research council consists of:
2 a. The commissioner of commerce or the commissioner's designee.
3 b. Two members with a substantial interest in medical devices appointed by the
4 attorney general.
5 c. Two members with a substantial interest in pharmaceuticals appointed by the
6 governor.
7 d. Two members with a substantial interest in biotechnology appointed by the
8 agriculture commissioner.
9 2. Subject to subsection 6, the term of office for members of the council is three years
10 but of those first appointed, two serve for one year, two serve for two years, and two
11 serve for three years.
12 3. The commissioner of commerce shall serve as chairman.
13 4. The council shall have at least one regular meeting each year and such additional
14 meetings as the chairman determines necessary at a time and place to be fixed by the
15 chairman. A special meeting must be called by the chairman on written request of any
16 three members. Four members constitute a quorum.
17 5. The council shall recommend to the industrial commission the approval of grants,
18 loans, or other financial assistance necessary or appropriate for funding, research,
19 development, marketing, and educational projects or activities and any other matters
20 related to this chapter.
21 6. Members of the council serve at the pleasure of the governor.
22 Access to council records.
23 1. Materials and data submitted to, or made or received by, the council or industrial
24 commission, to the extent the council or industrial commission determines the
25 materials or data consist of trade secrets or commercial, financial, or proprietary
26 information of individuals or entities applying to or contracting with the commission or
27 receiving council or industrial commission services under this chapter, are subject to
28 section 44 - 04 - 18.4 .
29 2. A person shall file a request with the council or industrial commission to have material
30 designated as confidential under subsection 1. The request must contain any
31 information required by the council or industrial commission and must include:
