1 a. A general description of the nature of the information sought to be protected.
2 b. An explanation of why the information derives independent economic value,
3 actual or potential, from not being generally known to others.
4 c. An explanation of why the information is not readily ascertainable by proper
5 means by others.
6 d. A general description of a person that may obtain economic value from disclosure
7 or use of the information, and how the person may obtain that value.
8 e. A description of the efforts used to maintain the secrecy of the information.
9 3. The information submitted under subsection 2 is confidential. The council or industria l
10 commission shall examine the request and determine whether the information is
11 relevant to the matter at hand and is a trade secret under the definition in section
12 44 - 04 - 18.4 or 47 - 25.1 - 01. If the council or industrial commission determines the
13 information is either not relevant or not a trade secret, the council or industrial
14 commission shall notify the requester and the requester may ask for the return of the
15 information and request within ten days of the notice. If no return is sought, the
16 information and request are a public record.
17 4. The names or identities of independent technical reviewers on a project or program
18 and the names of council members making recommendations are confidential, may
19 not be disclosed by the council, and are not public records subject to section 44 - 04 - 18
20 or section 6 of article XI of the Constitution of North Dakota .
21 Industrial commission powers.
22 1. The industrial commission may:
23 a Make a grant or loan, and provide other forms of financial assistance as
24 necessary or appropriate, to a qualified person for funding research,
25 development, marketing, and educational projects or activities, feasibility studies,
26 applied research and demonstrations, venture capital investments, and
27 low - interest loans and loan buydowns to foster the development of the life
28 science industry. Any financial assistance the commission awards to a project
29 may not be the project's sole support. Any financial assistance the commission
30 awards must be conditioned on the assurance the applicant or a third party will
