12 grants, or contributions from any department, agency, or instrumentality of the
13 United States for any purpose consistent with this chapter.
14 g. Establish interest buydown programs for equipment needed to development the
15 life science industry in the state.
16 h. Fund technical assistance from the university system and private entities to
17 producers.
18 2. The industrial commission may contract with the department of commerce to provide
19 technical assistance to the life science research council and the industrial commission
20 to carry out the purposes of this chapter, including pursuit of aid, grants, or
21 contributions of money or other things of value from any source for any purpose
22 consistent with this chapter. The department may contract with a public or private third
23 party to provide the technical assistance necessary to implement the purposes of this
24 chapter.
25 Life science development fund - Continuing appropriation.
26 The life science development fund is a special fund in the state treasury. All funds in the life
27 science development fund are appropriated to the industrial commission on a continuing basis
28 for the purpose of carrying out this chapter. Interest earned by the fund must be credited to the
29 fund.
30 SECTION 2. REPEAL. Section 4.1-01-20.1 of the North Dakota Century Code is repealed.
